  "prompt": "How do I stop procrastinating and wasting time?",
  "response": "Here are some effective strategies to stop procrastinating:\n\n1. Break tasks into smaller, manageable steps\n- Makes large tasks less overwhelming\n- Creates a sense of progress\n\n2. Use the \"Two-Minute Rule\"\n- If a task takes less than two minutes, do it immediately\n- Prevents small tasks from piling up\n\n3. Create a structured schedule\n- Set specific times for work and breaks\n- Use time-blocking techniques\n\n4. Eliminate distractions\n- Put phone on silent\n- Use website blockers\n- Create a dedicated workspace\n\n5. Practice the Pomodoro Technique\n- Work for 25 minutes\n- Take a 5-minute break\n- Repeat\n\n6. Set clear, realistic goals\n- Use SMART goal framework\n- Write down objectives\n\n7. Use accountability methods\n- Tell someone your goals\n- Find an accountability partner\n- Use habit-tracking apps\n\n8. Address underlying issues\n- Identify why you're procrastinating\n- Manage anxiety or perfectionism\n- Consider professional help if needed\n\n9. Reward yourself\n- Celebrate small accomplishments\n- Create positive reinforcement\n\n10. Practice self-compassion\n- Don't be too hard on yourself\n- Learn from setbacks\n\nConsistent practice and patience are key to overcoming procrastination.",
